    <!-- Activities Section -->
    <section class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our Activities</h2>
        
        <div class="activity-container">
            <!-- Activity 1 -->
            <div class="activity">
                <img src="images/kayaking.jpg" alt="Kayaking">
                <div class="activity-content">
                    <h3>Kayaking</h3>
                    <p>Kayaking is the use of a kayak for moving over water. It is distinguished from canoeing by the sitting position of the paddler and the number of blades on the paddle. Experience the serene waters of Phewa Lake with our guided kayaking tours.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Learn More</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Activity 2 -->
            <div class="activity">
                <img src="images/bungee.jpg" alt="Bungee">
                <div class="activity-content">
                    <h3>Bungee Jumping</h3>
                    <p>Bungee jumping is an activity that involves a person jumping from a great height while connected to a large elastic cord. Experience the ultimate adrenaline rush with Nepal's highest bungee jump at 160m above the Bhote Koshi river.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Learn More</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Activity 3 -->
            <div class="activity">
                <img src="images/zipline.jpg" alt="Zipline">
                <div class="activity-content">
                    <h3>Zipline</h3>
                    <p>Zip lining is an action-filled recreational activity that involves riding a steel cable on a protective seat between two points. Try the longest and steepest zip line in the world at Pokhara, spanning 1.8km with a vertical drop of 600m.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Learn More</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Activity 4 -->
            <div class="activity">
                <img src="images/images.jpg" alt="Rafting">
                <div class="activity-content">
                    <h3>Rafting</h3>
                    <p>Rafting in Pokhara involves navigating inflatable rafts through the waters of the Seti River. It's a popular activity for both experienced rafters and beginners, with rapids ranging from Grade II to Grade IV depending on the season.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Learn More</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Activity 5 -->
            <div class="activity">
                <img src="images/paragliding.jpg" alt="Paragliding">
                <div class="activity-content">
                    <h3>Paragliding</h3>
                    <p>Experience the thrill of flying over Pokhara with breathtaking views of the Himalayas and Phewa Lake. Pokhara is one of the best paragliding destinations in the world, with reliable thermals and stunning scenery.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Learn More</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Activity 6 -->
            <div class="activity">
                <img src="images/ultralight.jpg" alt="Ultralight Flight">
                <div class="activity-content">
                    <h3>Ultralight Flight</h3>
                    <p>Get a bird's eye view of Pokhara and the Annapurna range with an ultralight flight. This once-in-a-lifetime experience offers unparalleled views of the Himalayas, lakes, and landscapes of the Pokhara valley.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Learn More</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

